org.cpsolver.ifs.assignment

Class AssignmentAbstract<V extends Variable<V,T>,T extends Value<V,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cpsolver.ifs.assignment.AssignmentAbstract<V,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - Variable
    T - Value
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Assignment<V,T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AssignmentArray, AssignmentMap, DefaultParallelAssignment, DefaultSingleAssignment, EmptyAssignment, OptimisticInheritedAssignment

    public abstract class AssignmentAbstract<V extends Variable<V,T>,T extends Value<V,T>>
extends Object
implements Assignment<V,T>
    An abstract implementation of an Assignment object. It contains an instance of a given assignment context holder (see AssignmentContextHolder) and implements the assignment logic. But the actual process of storing and retrieving values is left on the assignment implementation.
    Version:
    IFS 1.3 (Iterative Forward Search)
